<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="55" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Sialidae" genus="Ilyobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ilyobius flavicollis" order="Megaloptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicollis">Ilyobius flavicollis</taxonomicName>
is the type species of the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Sialidae" genus="Ilyobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ilyobius" order="Megaloptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ilyobius</taxonomicName>
. Unfortunately, the primary type of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Sialidae" genus="Ilyobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ilyobius flavicollis" order="Megaloptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicollis">Ilyobius flavicollis</taxonomicName>
is largely damaged with the abdomen lost. Nevertheless, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Sialidae" genus="Ilyobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ilyobius flavicollis" order="Megaloptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicollis">Ilyobius flavicollis</taxonomicName>
is highly possible to be the same genus with the other Neotropical alderflies based on the alternately black-orange body coloration and the wing venations with two simple Rs branches and a bifurcated posterior branch of MP. The cephalic color pattern of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Sialidae" genus="Ilyobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ilyobius flavicollis" order="Megaloptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicollis">Ilyobius flavicollis</taxonomicName>
is different from all the other 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Sialidae" genus="Ilyobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ilyobius" order="Megaloptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ilyobius</taxonomicName>
species, suggesting that this species should be valid.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
